videos.description: With Duke going for it on fourth and one from Miami's 13, Michael Pickney sacks Daniel Jones for a loss of 11 and a turnover on downs.
videos.headline: Miami defense gets 4th down stop in red zone

videos.description: Mark Walton takes a short pass from Malik Rosier and jumps over a Duke defender en route to a 39-yard pickup.
videos.headline: Miami's Walton hurdles defender on big gain

videos.description: Braxton Berrios beats his man and Malik Rosier connects with him over the middle for a 27-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Miami strikes first as Rosier finds Berrios

videos.description: Malik Rosier gets the Miami offense up the to line quickly, and scores on a QB sneak from one yard out.
videos.headline: Rosier sneaks it in for Hurricanes TD

videos.description: Duke QB Daniel Jones has his pass tipped, then intercepted by Michael Pinckney, who lays out to make the grab.
videos.headline: Pinckney makes diving catch for Miami INT

videos.description: Braxton Berrios puts a move on his man to get open, and Malik Rosier finds him along the sideline for a 25-yard gain, leading to a Miami field goal.
videos.headline: Berrios burns his man, puts Canes in red zone

videos.description: Miami coach Mark Richt says "it's huge" that his team has limited Duke to just two field goals in the first half, as the Hurricanes head into the break with a 17-6 lead.
videos.headline: Richt pleased with Miami's defensive effort in first half

videos.description: Miami punter Zach Feagles wishes he could have this punt back, as his kick actually goes backwards for a 1-yard loss.
videos.headline: Miami punt goes horribly wrong

videos.description: Miami QB Malik Rosier overthrows his target, and Blue Devils' CB Bryon Fields Jr. is in the right place to intercept the pass.
videos.headline: Duke's Fields Jr. picks off Rosier

videos.description: Malik Rosier finds Ahmmon Richards on a short slant over the middle, and Richards takes it all the way to the house for a 49-yard touchdown, giving Miami a 24-6 lead.
videos.headline: Richards outruns the defense for long Canes TD

videos.description: Travis Homer takes a handoff and bursts through a big hole to score a 40-yard touchdown, extending Miami's lead.
videos.headline: Miami's Homer scores untouched from 40 yards out

videos.description: Miami's head coach Mark Richt is impressed with his team's 31-6 win over Duke and what they still need to improve on.
videos.headline: Richt is 'proud of everybody'

videos.description: Miami's Malik Rosier describes his second start as quarterback and how his this win was an altogether team victory that will prepare the team for Florida State next weekend.
videos.headline: Rosier looking forward to FSU next weekend

videos.description: Mack Brown and Dave LaMount lay out how the Hurricane's defense was the driving factor in Miami's 31-6 victory over the Devils.
videos.headline: Defense carries Miami past Duke
